    "id": "choose-template",
    "title": "Step 1 — Choosing a template",
    "html": "<p>This first step is where you pick the kind of document you want to make. DocForge builds the same document for every student on your list, so start by choosing the right one.</p>\n\n<h3>Pick a template</h3>\n<p>On the <strong>Choose a template</strong> screen you'll see a set of cards, each with a name and a short description. The cards are sorted into groups so they're easy to find:</p>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr><th>Group</th><th>Templates in it</th></tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td><strong>Certificates</strong></td><td><code>Classic certificate</code> — award certificate, A4 landscape</td></tr>\n<tr><td><strong>Reports</strong></td><td><code>Progress report</code> — per-subject marks and a teacher comment</td></tr>\n<tr><td><strong>Finance</strong></td><td><code>Fee receipt</code> — a payment receipt</td></tr>\n<tr><td><strong>Cards</strong></td><td><code>Student ID card</code> — ID card with a QR code</td></tr>\n<tr><td><strong>Letters</strong></td><td><code>Attendance letter</code> and <code>Enrollment confirmation</code></td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>To choose one, just <strong>click its card</strong>. The selected card is highlighted so you can see what's chosen. Changed your mind? Click a different card.</p>\n\n<h3>Move on to the next step</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Click the template card you want.</li>\n<li>Click the <code>Continue</code> button at the bottom right.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The <code>Continue</code> button stays greyed out until you've picked a template, so if you can't click it yet, choose a card first.</p>\n\n<div class=\"tip\">\n<p>Not sure which one to pick? Read the short description under each name — it tells you what the finished document looks like (for example, <code>Per-subject marks + comment, A4 portrait</code> for the <code>Progress report</code>). You can always come back and switch templates later by clicking <code>Back</code> to return to this step.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"note\">\n<p>Each template asks for its own details — a <code>Classic certificate</code> needs a <code>Recipient name</code> and an <code>Award</code>, while a <code>Fee receipt</code> needs a <code>Student name</code> and an <code>Amount</code>. To see exactly which fields each template uses (and which ones are required), see the <strong>Template reference</strong> section.</p>\n</div>",
