    "id": "templates-reference",
    "title": "Template reference",
    "html": "<p>DocForge has six ready-made templates. This page lists every one, what it produces, and the exact fields it uses. The <strong>field names below are the labels you map your spreadsheet columns to</strong> when you set up a batch. Fields marked <strong>Required</strong> must be matched to a column, or DocForge cannot create that document.</p>\n\n<div class=\"tip\">A field that is <em>not</em> required can be left unmapped. It simply stays blank on the finished document, so you only need columns for the parts you actually use.</div>\n\n<h3>Classic certificate</h3>\n<p>Award certificate, A4 landscape. Grouped under <code>Certificates</code>.</p>\n<table>\n<thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Required?</th></tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td><code>Recipient name</code></td><td><strong>Required</strong></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Award</code></td><td><strong>Required</strong></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Detail / citation</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Teacher</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Date</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>School</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Special behaviour:</strong> the certificate header (your logo and school name) can sit on the <em>left</em>, <em>center</em>, or <em>right</em>. You set this with the <code>Header position</code> control in the branding panel, which appears only for this template. It defaults to <em>center</em>.</p>\n\n<h3>Progress report</h3>\n<p>Per-subject marks and a teacher comment, A4 portrait. Grouped under <code>Reports</code>.</p>\n<table>\n<thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Required?</th></tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td><code>Student name</code></td><td><strong>Required</strong></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Class</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Term</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Teacher comment</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Teacher</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Date</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Special behaviour:</strong> this is the only template that uses <strong>subject columns</strong>. On top of the fields above, you tick which spreadsheet columns hold marks (for example <code>Maths</code>, <code>English</code>, <code>Science</code>). Each one you tick becomes a row in the marks table, with the column name as the subject and the cell value as the mark. Only columns not already mapped to a field can be ticked as subjects.</p>\n<div class=\"note\">If you tick no subject columns, the marks table prints a reminder that no subjects were selected instead of any marks. Tick at least one subject column before generating progress reports.</div>\n\n<h3>Fee receipt</h3>\n<p>Payment receipt, A4 portrait. Grouped under <code>Finance</code>.</p>\n<table>\n<thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Required?</th></tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td><code>Student name</code></td><td><strong>Required</strong></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Receipt no.</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Fee type</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Amount</code></td><td><strong>Required</strong></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Amount paid</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Balance</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Payment method</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Date</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Received by</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div class=\"tip\">If you leave <code>Amount paid</code> blank, the receipt shows the full <code>Amount</code> as paid. <code>Balance</code> shows as <code>0</code> when empty, and <code>Fee type</code> reads <em>Tuition fee</em> by default.</div>\n\n<h3>Student ID card</h3>\n<p>ID card with a QR code, CR80 (standard card size). Grouped under <code>Cards</code>.</p>\n<table>\n<thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Required?</th></tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td><code>Full name</code></td><td><strong>Required</strong></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Student ID</code></td><td><strong>Required</strong></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Class</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Valid until</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Special behaviour:</strong> the <code>Student ID</code> value is turned into a <strong>scannable QR code</strong> printed on the card, and the same ID is shown as text beneath it. So make sure each student's <code>Student ID</code> is correct and unique.</p>\n\n<h3>Attendance letter</h3>\n<p>Attendance notice, A4 portrait. Grouped under <code>Letters</code>.</p>\n<table>\n<thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Required?</th></tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td><code>Student name</code></td><td><strong>Required</strong></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Class</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Attendance %</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Days absent</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Period</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Guardian name</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Message</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Signed by</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Date</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div class=\"tip\">If you fill in <code>Guardian name</code>, the letter greets that person by name; otherwise it opens with <em>Dear Parent / Guardian</em>. Leave <code>Message</code> blank to use the standard attendance wording, or supply your own.</div>\n\n<h3>Enrollment confirmation</h3>\n<p>Admission confirmation, A4 portrait. Grouped under <code>Letters</code>.</p>\n<table>\n<thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Required?</th></tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td><code>Student name</code></td><td><strong>Required</strong></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Class / grade</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Academic year</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Status</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Admission no.</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Signed by</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>Date</code></td><td>Optional</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div class=\"tip\">Leave <code>Status</code> blank and the letter reads that the student is <em>confirmed</em> for enrollment. Fill it in (for example <em>provisionally accepted</em>) to change that wording.</div>",
